<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id80e33d93-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c" identifier="/us/usc/t40/s14702"><num value="14702">§ 14702.</num><heading> Nondiscrimination</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">An individual in the United States shall not, because of sex, be excluded from participation in, be denied the benefits of, or be subjected to discrimination under, a program or activity receiving federal financial assistance under this subtitle.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id80e33d94-3a70-11f1-b817-c08bf6d1fe2c">(<ref href="/us/pl/107/217">Pub. L. 107–217</ref>, <date date="2002-08-21">Aug. 21, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/1278">116 Stat. 1278</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
